hopobject.body: I'm doing a masters in law ssphealth.com MEK members within Iraq were largely disarmed after the 2003 American invasion. The group had been granted protection by Saddam Hussein before the invasion and lived at Camp Ashraf for two decades. After the U.S. troop withdrawal in 2009, many group members moved in 2012 from Camp Ashraf to Camp Liberty, an abandoned U.S. military base. As Iraq spins yet again into regular violence, the disarmed militants and their families are among the victims.
